Parliament, Monday, 26 August 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Home Affairs will over the next week visit the Department of Home Affairs Offices, the Independent Electoral Commission (IEC) of South Africa and the Government Printing Works as part of its oversight responsibility. The primary aim of the visit is to scrutinise the priorities of the Department and entities that report to it in the sixth administration. This includes analysing and understanding the application regime governed by the Immigration Act and how the department aims to deal with the challenge of long queues and delayed approval processes. The committee will on the first day visit the Desmond Tutu Refugee Reception Centre and BVR building. Details of the visit: Date: 27 August 2019
	Venue: 14th Floor, Hallmark Building, 230 Johannes Ramokhoase St, Pretoria
	Time: 8:30 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON HOME AFFAIRS, ADV BONGANI BONGO. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
